Here are both approaches.

### 1. Register the route in `AppShell.xaml.cs`

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

### 2. Navigate from `ProductListPage`

```csharp
// Approach A — string ID via query string
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");
}

// Approach B — full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

### 3. Receive data in the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product  { get => _product;  set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter arrives as object, call ToString()
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using ProductId...
        }

        // Approach B — complex object, cast directly
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?productId=...`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| Data type | String only | Any object |
| Serialization | Automatic to/from string | None — passed by reference |
| Deep-link friendly | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| Best for | IDs, simple values | Full objects already in memory |

Both approaches call `ApplyQueryAttributes` exactly once after navigation, so you can handle them in the same method as shown above. Always `await` the `GoToAsync` call to avoid race conditions.
